        {
          "message_type": "system",
          "message_text": "Fluevog: Get your funk on! The NEW Fluevog x George Clinton collection has arrived, and it\u0027s funkadelic! Shop now: https://usvog.attn.tv/aJMRg2SqkEVu ",
          "date_time": "2024-05-31 12:35:36.867",
          "message_media": [
            
          ]
        },
        {
          "message_type": "system",
          "message_text": "Fluevog: FLASH SALE! Take an EXTRA 30% OFF all sale styles! But hurry! Offer ends Monday, June 10. Shop now to secure your faves: https://usvog.attn.tv/aix61hb4319k ",
          "date_time": "2024-06-07 14:06:58.017",
          "message_media": [
            
          ]
        },
        {
          "message_type": "system",
          "message_text": "Fluevog: HURRY! Extra 30% off all sale ends TONIGHT. Don\u0027t let your feet stay sad! Shop now: https://usvog.attn.tv/aTYv6QvZW2BN ",
          "date_time": "2024-06-10 20:02:30.188",
          "message_media": [
            
          ]
        },
        {
          "message_type": "system",
          "message_text": "Fluevog: Hey, this is Jordan. Thanks for checking out our site! https://usvog.attn.tv/aM0BQKQxjtXO \n\nIs there anything I can help you find today? (I won\u0027t tell your other shoes.)",
          "date_time": "2024-06-12 12:04:21.238",
          "message_media": [
            
          ]
        },
        {
          "message_type": "customer",
          "message_text": "Somehow I didn\u0027t see this until just now! Sorry about that. I was looking at the Cadet boot, and am tempted, but I worry a bit about the foot bed. I have several pairs of Fluvog shoes sitting in a closet because their foot beds are too narrow. However, the 7th Heaven foot beds work well for me. What is the Cadet\u0027s foot bed like?",
          "date_time": "2024-06-18 16:39:23.923",
          "message_media": [
            
          ]
        },
        {
          "message_id": "01902d19-6e68-4c07-f000-000003f49daa",
          "message_text": "Fluevog: Thanks for letting me know, and no problem at all! If you\u0027re referring to these boots - https://usvog.attn.tv/aaKIpG37HVQl These run small and narrow. We suggest sizing up by a half-size, or a full size for wider feet. The removable insole may be too thick, making the boots fit 1/2 size smaller. Without it, they fit true to size and give extra toe room. You can replace the insole with a thinner one if needed. If you\u0027re between sizes, it\u0027s best to size up. \n\nOur shoe fitting is very specific to the style of the shoe. I\u0027d also recommend checking out the reviews on the product page as some shoes have quite a few reviews to help you with sizing questions. If you\u0027re still in doubt, let me know the size you usually wear so I can check on this with the team for you!",
          "message_type": "agent",
          "agent": "46578",
          "message_media": [
            
          ],
          "date_time": "2024-06-18 16:45:59.799"
        },
        {
          "message_type": "customer",
          "message_text": "Those are indeed the shoes! It\u0027s good to know about the small and narrow fit. \n\nMy Super Vogs are all 9s, and fit like a dream. I have some that read \"Future Angel\" on the soles that are also 9s, and are comfortable. I have a pair that says \"Dadio\" on the sole that at 8.5 I can barely squeeze my foot into, and a dressier shoe that is an 8.5 and is tight, but wearable. I\u0027m not sure of the style name, but I can send you pictures if that would help.",
          "date_time": "2024-06-18 16:59:13.543",
          "message_media": [
            
          ]
        },
        {
          "message_type": "customer",
          "message_text": "Oh. One pair of supervogs is an 8.5. it fits well, though.",
          "date_time": "2024-06-18 17:06:53.275",
          "message_media": [
            
          ]
        },
        {
          "message_id": "01902d2d-71a9-45fa-f000-000003f49daa",
          "message_text": "Fluevog: Our shoe fittings are specific to each style, so I recommend checking out the reviews on the product page as some shoes have several reviews that can provide helpful insights on sizing.\n\nRegarding the Manifold Cadet Fluevog X Star Trek: Strange New Worlds, these shoes tend to fit small and narrow in the toe area. We suggest going half a size up from your usual size. If you have wider feet, consider sizing up by a whole size. It\u0027s worth noting that these boots feature a removable insole that may be too thick for some wearers.\n\nFor example, if you typically wear size 9 Vogfs, I would recommend getting size 9.5 or even 10 if your feet are wider.",
          "message_type": "agent",
          "agent": "82259",
          "message_media": [
            
          ],
          "date_time": "2024-06-18 17:07:51.349"
        }
      ]
    },
